<i>noun</i>: 환송 [환송], 하직 [하ː직], 작별 [작뼐], 이별 [이ː별], 송별 [송ː별], 고별 [고ː별] <br>
<ul>
<li><i>noun</i><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>환송 [환송]</dt><br>
<dd>farewell; saying good-bye</dd><br>
<dd>떠나는 사람을 기쁜 마음으로 보냄.</dd><br>
<dd>The act of sending off with pleasure someone who is leaving.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>하직 [하ː직]</dt><br>
<dd>1. farewell; good-bye</dd><br>
<dd>먼 길을 떠날 때 웃어른께 작별을 고하는 인사.</dd><br>
<dd>The act of bidding farewell to elders when one is about to take a long journey.</dd><br>
<dd>2. ending; quitting; resignation</dd><br>
<dd>어떤 일을 마지막으로 하거나 그만둠.</dd><br>
<dd>The act of doing something for the last time, or quitting it.</dd><br>
<dd>3. passing away; parting; leaving</dd><br>
<dd>죽어서 세상을 떠남.</dd><br>
<dd>An act of dying and leaving this world.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>작별 [작뼐]</dt><br>
<dd>farewell; parting; separation</dd><br>
<dd>서로 인사를 나누고 헤어짐.</dd><br>
<dd>The act of exchanging good-byes and parting with each other.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>이별 [이ː별]</dt><br>
<dd>parting; separation; farewell</dd><br>
<dd>오랫동안 만나지 못하게 떨어져 있거나 헤어짐.</dd><br>
<dd>The act of separating or parting from someone so that one cannot see him/her for a long time.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>송별 [송ː별]</dt><br>
<dd>farewell; send-off</dd><br>
<dd>떠나는 사람을 보냄.</dd><br>
<dd>The act of sending off a person who is leaving.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>고별 [고ː별]</dt><br>
<dd>1. farewell</dd><br>
<dd>같이 있던 사람들에게 헤어짐을 알림.</dd><br>
<dd>Announcing to coworkers, an audience, etc., that one is leaving.</dd><br>
<dd>2. paying homage to the deceased</dd><br>
<dd>장례식에서 죽은 사람에게 이별을 알림.</dd><br>
<dd>In a funeral, saying good-bye to the deceased.</dd><br>
</li>
</ul>